generatedSentence: Under a sky where a rare celestial syzygy cast a glowing, ethereal light, the opulent halls of aristocrats, still adorned with polished quartz and the faint, sweet scent of pyrolyzed incense, were sinking into an accelerating implosion of their own making, fueled by the oppressive authoritarianism of a failing monarchy that was being quizzed by the rumbling revolution, which aimed to maximize distribution beyond mere meat and produce for the privileged bourgeoisie who still casually devoured their flapjack breakfasts; as bells tolled a jazzy, discordant knell, signaling the death of feudalism and the rise of raw capitalism, the proletariat, once chained by scarcity, longed to oxygenize their futures while stargazing past the impending anarchy to a new understanding of economics.
